Preheat your oven to 375°F (190°C).
Prepare Vegetables:

Peel and thinly slice the potatoes, sweet potatoes, carrots, and parsnips. Thin slices ensure even cooking.
Sauté Onions and Garlic:

In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add sliced onions and minced garlic. Sauté until the onions are translucent and aromatic. Set aside.
Assemble the Tian:

Grease a baking dish with olive oil. Arrange the sliced vegetables in layers, alternating between the potatoes, sweet potatoes, carrots, parsnips, and sautéed onions and garlic. Season each layer with salt, pepper, and dried thyme.
Pour Broth:

Pour vegetable or chicken broth over the layered vegetables. This adds moisture and helps in the cooking process.
Cover and Bake:

Cover the baking dish with aluminum foil and bake in the preheated oven for about 45-55 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Optional Cheese Topping:

If desired, uncover the tian during the last 15 minutes of baking and sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top. This will create a golden, cheesy crust.
Garnish and Serve:

Once the vegetables are tender, remove the tian from the oven. Garnish with fresh chopped parsley and let it rest for a few minutes before serving.
Serve Warm:

Serve the root vegetable tian warm as a side dish or as a main course. It pairs well with a green salad or grilled protein."
